UMPA demo

UMPA demo#

Demonstrating the use of the implementation of the Unified Modulated Pattern Analysis package (UMPA).

import numpy as np
from matplotlib import pyplot as plt
import h5py
%matplotlib widget

# Load data (in hdf5 format)
with h5py.File('sphere_toothpick_prepared_0.6.h5') as f:
    ref = f['ref'][:]
    sam = f['sam'][:]

plt.figure()
plt.imshow(sam.mean(axis=0)/ref.mean(axis=0))

# Blinking reference / sample 
import matplotlib.animation

sam_ROI = sam[0][300:400,650:750]
ref_ROI = ref[0][300:400,650:750]
fig = plt.figure()
img = plt.imshow(sam_ROI)

def animate(i):
    if i==0:
        img.set_data(ref_ROI)
    else:
        img.set_data(sam_ROI)

ani = matplotlib.animation.FuncAnimation(fig, animate, frames=2)

from IPython.display import HTML
plt.close()
HTML(ani.to_jshtml())

import UMPA

M = UMPA.model.UMPAModelDF(sam, ref, window_size=2)

result = M.match(step=2)
